      <h4>The Pomodoro Technique</h4>
      <div id="pomodoro">
        <div id="pomodoro-timer">
          <h3>Pomodoro Timer</h3>
          <div id="timer">25:00</div>
          <button id="startButton" class="btn btn-primary">Start</button>
          <button id="resetButton" class="btn btn-secondary">Reset</button>
        </div>
        <p>
          The Pomodoro Technique, a time management method developed by
          Francesco Cirillo, is an invaluable tool for students seeking enhanced
          productivity and focus. Inspired by a tomato-shaped kitchen timer, the
          method employs short, structured intervals, traditionally 25 minutes
          in duration, known as "Pomodoros." Each Pomodoro is followed by a
          brief break, fostering sustained concentration and preventing burnout.
          For students, the Pomodoro Technique proves particularly effective in
          tackling challenging study sessions. By breaking down complex tasks
          into manageable intervals, learners can maintain optimal cognitive
          function while minimizing fatigue.
        </p>
